---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Spousal Support & Alimony Attorneys Maryland | Divorce With A Plan"
  description="Maryland spousal support and alimony attorneys. Whether seeking or contesting alimony, our Rockville and Baltimore attorneys build evidence-based arguments under Maryland law."
  ogTitle="Spousal Support & Alimony Attorneys Maryland | Divorce With A Plan"
  ogDescription="Experienced Maryland alimony attorneys. We fight for fair spousal support — whether you're seeking it or contesting it. Free consultation available."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 to-slate-700 text-white py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto text-center">
      <p class="text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-widest text-sm font-semibold mb-3">Maryland Spousal Support Attorneys</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6 leading-tight">
        Spousal Support That Reflects<br class="hidden md:block" />
        Your True Circumstances
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-slate-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">
        Whether you need alimony to maintain financial stability after divorce or you're contesting an unreasonable support demand, our Maryland attorneys build strong, evidence-based cases that account for your real financial picture.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/free-consultation" class="bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-white font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Schedule Free Consultation
        </a>
        <a href="tel:2402693592" class="border-2 border-white hover:bg-white hover:text-slate-900 text-white font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Call (240) 269-3592
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Types of Spousal Support -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Types of Spousal Support in Maryland</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Maryland law recognizes several types of alimony, each serving a different purpose and governed by specific rules.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {[
          {
            title: "Pendente Lite Alimony",
            subtitle: "Temporary Support During Divorce",
            desc: "Awarded while the divorce is pending, pendente lite alimony provides immediate financial support to a lower-earning spouse to help maintain the marital standard of living during proceedings.",
            icon: "⏳"
          },
          {
            title: "Rehabilitative Alimony",
            subtitle: "Time-Limited Support for Reentry",
            desc: "The most common form — designed to support a spouse while they gain education, training, or work experience to become self-sufficient. Awarded for a specific time period.",
            icon: "📚"
          },
          {
            title: "Indefinite Alimony",
            subtitle: "Long-Term or Permanent Support",
            desc: "Granted in cases of long marriages or when a spouse cannot reasonably become self-sufficient due to age, disability, or illness. The court may also award indefinite alimony when a significant disparity in standards of living would otherwise result.",
            icon: "♾️"
          }
        ].map(type => (
          <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-3">{type.icon}</div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">{type.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-amber-600 text-sm font-medium mb-3">{type.subtitle}</p>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">{type.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How MD Courts Determine Alimony -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-5">How Maryland Courts Determine Alimony</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
            Maryland courts have broad discretion in awarding spousal support. Unlike child support, there is no formula — judges weigh a comprehensive set of statutory factors to reach a determination that is fair under the specific circumstances of each case.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
            This means the outcome depends heavily on how your case is presented. The quality of your financial documentation, the credibility of your testimony, and the legal arguments your attorney makes all play a critical role.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            Our attorneys at Divorce With A Plan prepare meticulously for spousal support hearings and trials — compiling financial records, income documentation, and lifestyle evidence to build the strongest possible case for our clients.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Statutory Factors Courts Consider</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            {[
              "Ability of the requesting spouse to be self-supporting",
              "Time needed for education or training to enable employment",
              "Standard of living established during the marriage",
              "Duration of the marriage",
              "Contributions of each party to the marital home (monetary & non-monetary)",
              "Circumstances contributing to the estrangement",
              "Age and physical/mental condition of each party",
              "Ability of the paying spouse to meet their own needs while paying alimony",
              "Financial needs and resources of each party",
              "Agreement between the parties"
            ].map(factor => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-500 font-bold mt-0.5">✓</span>
                <span class="text-slate-700 text-sm">{factor}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Seeking vs. Contesting -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">We Represent Both Sides</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Whether you're seeking spousal support or fighting an unreasonable demand, our strategy is tailored to your specific situation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-8 border-l-4 border-amber-500">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">If You're Seeking Alimony</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-4">We help you document and present the strongest possible case for spousal support — including your financial needs, marital contributions, and the lifestyle established during marriage.</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            {[
              "Documenting your financial needs with specificity",
              "Establishing your non-monetary marital contributions",
              "Showing the income disparity between the parties",
              "Arguing for appropriate duration and amount",
              "Seeking pendente lite support to sustain you during proceedings"
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
                <span class="text-amber-500">✓</span> {item}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-8 border-l-4 border-slate-400">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">If You're Contesting Alimony</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-4">We challenge excessive or unwarranted alimony demands by presenting your financial circumstances clearly and holding the requesting spouse to the statutory burden of proof.</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            {[
              "Accurately presenting your income and financial obligations",
              "Challenging your spouse's self-sufficiency claims",
              "Documenting their earning capacity and opportunities",
              "Arguing for limited duration rather than indefinite alimony",
              "Seeking modification or termination of existing orders"
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
                <span class="text-slate-500">✓</span> {item}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Modification & Termination -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-5">Modifying or Terminating Alimony</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
            Alimony orders don't always remain appropriate as circumstances change. Maryland law allows for modification or termination of spousal support when there has been a <strong>material change in circumstances</strong>.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
            Common grounds for modification include significant changes in either party's income, job loss, remarriage of the recipient spouse, cohabitation, or health changes.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            Our attorneys handle both <strong>seeking modification</strong> (when you need more support or different terms) and <strong>defending against modification</strong> (when your current support arrangement is being challenged).
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Common Grounds for Modification</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            {[
              { label: "Job loss or significant income reduction", party: "Payor" },
              { label: "Significant increase in payor's income", party: "Recipient" },
              { label: "Recipient's remarriage (often terminates support)", party: "Payor" },
              { label: "Recipient's cohabitation with a romantic partner", party: "Payor" },
              { label: "Recipient becomes self-sufficient", party: "Payor" },
              { label: "Serious illness or disability", party: "Either" }
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start justify-between gap-3">
                <span class="text-slate-700 text-sm">{item.label}</span>
                <span class="text-xs bg-slate-100 text-slate-500 px-2 py-1 rounded flex-shrink-0">{item.party}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-amber-500">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Get Spousal Support Representation That Fights for You</h2>
      <p class="text-amber-100 mb-8 text-lg">Our Maryland alimony attorneys are ready to evaluate your case. Schedule your free consultation today.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/free-consultation" class="bg-white text-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-50 font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Book Free Consultation
        </a>
        <a href="tel:2402693592" class="border-2 border-white text-white hover:bg-amber-600 font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">
          (240) 269-3592
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
